results.name: Permutations with exactly 11 fixed points.
link: Vincenzo Librandi, Table of n, a(n) for n = 11..200
maple: restart: G(x):=exp(-x)/(1-x)*(x^11/11!): f[0]:=G(x): for n from 1 to 29 do f[n]:=diff(f[n-1],x) od: x:=0: seq(f[n],n=11..27); # _Zerinvary Lajos_, Apr 03 2009
mathematica: With[{nn=40}, Drop[CoefficientList[Series[Exp[-x]/(1 - x) x^11/11!, {x, 0, nn}], x]Range[0, nn]!, 11]] (* _Vincenzo Librandi_, Feb 19 2014 *)
